    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-04-05T17:05:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-04-05T17:05:00-05:00" n="676"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d676">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">357.AB/4–552: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Pakistan</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d676fn1">This telegram was repeated for information to
                        London and New York.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential<lb/>priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-04-05T17:05:00-05:00"
                            >April 5, 1952—5:05 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1018. Re Kashmir. <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> and <gloss
                        target="#t_Brit1">Brit</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> with UK <gloss target="#t_FonOff1"
                        >FonOff</gloss> approval are in agreement that the fol message shld be
                    conveyed by you to <gloss target="#t_GOP1">GOP</gloss> (the UK High Commissioner
                    will receive similar instructions): <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>We were impressed by wisdom <persName corresp="#p_KCSM1"
                                >Zafrullah</persName>’s suggestion that it was important to avoid
                            further formal stage (<gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> debate) before
                            negots by the parties with Dr. <persName corresp="#p_GDF1"
                                >Graham</persName> were resumed and that a continuing process of
                            negot shld be aimed at.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>Accordingly, we conveyed this suggestion to Dr. <persName
                                corresp="#p_GDF1">Graham</persName> at Geneva and commended it to
                            him.</item>
                        <pb facs="0167" n="1217" xml:id="pg_1217"/>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>We understand that Dr. <persName corresp="#p_GDF1">Graham</persName>
                            is returning to NY this weekend and we further understand that on
                            arrival before submitting any report, he wishes to hold further
                            discussions with the <gloss target="#t_REP1">rep</gloss>s of the parties
                            in NY.</item>
                        <label>4.</label>
                        <item>We hope that the Govt of <gloss target="#t_Pak1">Pak</gloss>,
                            recognizing the great importance of continuing their efforts to reach
                            agreement, will be ready to resume negots in this way, particularly in
                            view of the advantage of avoiding public debate at this stage.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_ADG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
